Genotype principal components for new individuals

Source: R/data.R
example_genopc_new.Rd

Principal component (PC) scores computed from genotype data for a set of new individuals. These individuals are projected into the same PC space as the training set to be used in the cell type proportion modeling.

Usage

data("example_genopc_new")

Format

A tibble with 982 rows and 31 columns:

indiv

Individual identifier (e.g., "NEW_SAMP1").

PC1, PC2, ..., PC30

Principal component scores for new individuals projected into the PC space derived from training individuals.

Examples

data("example_genopc_new")
